RACE.RACE_TEXT: Clark S. presented by Norton Healthcare - Grade2 CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 11 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 110. Stakes Purse 600000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRADEMARK tracked behind the leaders and from the two path, pursued from the pocket with run around the far turn, took aim on the leaders from the four path and among rivals entering the lane, rallied to bid at the furlong grounds, sparred through the late stages and narrowly prevailed. FIRST MISSION vied along the inside, led in upper stretch, shifted out to meet TRADEMARK's challenge at the furlong grounds, gamely battled with that one through the late stages but missed via a tight photo. IL MIRACOLO laid off of the pace in the two path, took closer order before pursuing in the three path into the far turn, shifted to the four path and between rivals turning for home before floating to the six path entering the lane, then stayed on while shifting inwardly and gained show from an outer foe at the sixteenth pole. BLUE DEVIL lacked speed along the inside, shifted to the five path entering the backstretch, pursued in the four path around the far turn, shifted ground outside of rivals passing the three sixteenths pole and ran on willingly. GASOLINE laid off of the pace in the three to four path around the first turn, pursued in the two to three path around the far turn, improved inside of rivals in upper stretch and failed to threaten. FILM STAR vied two wide but yielded between horses in upper stretch. STRAIGHT ARROW pursued from midpack in the two to three path around the far turn chased in the four path into the far turn, got floated five wide turning for home then fanned to the seven path entering the lane and tired. GIANT GAME stalked outside of the leading pair, but faded in the five path and between horses entering the lane. STAGE RAIDER broke erratically and bucked leaving the gates many lengths behind the rest, lagged behind around both turns then narrowed the gap through the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 12 1M Dirt CR: 81. Maiden Special Weight Purse 92000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. For Horses That Have Sold Or RNA for $50,000 Or Less At Their Most Recent Auction.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANIMAL FRIES stalked along the inside, bid inside of the leaders in upper stretch, led from an outer bidder into the final furlong and held sway. EYES OF GOLD advanced among foes leaving the chute to track two wide and between horses, tipped to the four path entering the lane, bid outside of the new leader in midstretch but was fended off through the final furlong. LIPOCHROME set the pace along the inside but yielded between bidders in upper stretch. LADAN pressed two wide, but gave way between horses in upper stretch. STAGFLATION pursued from midpack tow wide and between horses, shifted four wide at the three furlong pole, floated to the six path entering the lane and lacked a bid. STAGE BELL laid off of the pace under a snug hold along the inside and improved in upper stretcch. BLUE TOPAZ laid off of the pace while hung five wide, fanned seven wide into the lane and faded. SOUL HEIR was outrun in the three path. IMPERATOR FURIOSA stumbled at the start, tracked three wide, then weakened in the five path and between horses entering the lane.
